title: Nice and good food, a bit “machinery “ feeling
text:
Good and Italian, though in Norway.
Ok prices and friendly staff.
A bit loud and noisy
Ok price wise

title: Spooky, weird and very different
text:
A very special place, a bit hard to find and only open some Sunday’s..... so check out before having to return without a visit
It’s all dark in there and you have to get use to seeing in the almost darkness, but it’s well worth it!

title: Fantastic building, both inside and out!
text: This is defiantly one of the big musts when in Oslo. Stunning architecture, outside walk on (Italian) white marble and in side see the fabulous interior - and if possible, try to also get hold of tickets for an opera or ballet (all played in original language and texted in English (and Norwegian)

title: Lively, friendly and great wines!
text:
A cozy, little place, centrally, yet neither world behind the curtains
Haven’t eaten there, but restaurant also serves food that is supposed to be good!
Atmosphere great, wine by glass excellent and not too expensive
